Description
------------------

This course focuses on the concepts and skills essential for developing and
leading breakthrough work teams. Emphasis is placed on decision-making and
problem solving, inter-team and intra-team dynamics, team composition, and
organizational support and barriers to teams, as well as on current issues
such as virtual teams, self-managed teams, transnational teams, and high-
performance teams. Students are given the opportunity to gain an understanding
of team processes, and to assess and develop team skills through real world
team projects, experien-tial activities, self-assessment tools, and case
analysis.

